9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 439, L.D. 1021, “An Act to Remove
10 Certain Cost-of-living Adjustment Restrictions for Retired Members of the Law
11 Enforcement Bargaining Unit Who Are 65 Years of Age or Older”
12 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 2 and inserting the following:
13 'Sec. 2. 5 MRSA §17806, sub-§1, ¶A-4 is enacted to read:
14 A-4. Beginning in 2025, whenever there is a percentage increase in the Consumer
15 Price Index from July 1st to June 30th, the board shall automatically make an equal
16 percentage increase in retirement benefits, beginning in September, up to a maximum
17 annual increase of 3% for retirement benefits paid to individuals who are 65 years of
18 age or older and who retired from a position as a law enforcement officer as defined in
19 Title 25, section 2801-A, subsection 5 or from a probation or parole officer position as
20 described in Title 34-A, section 5404.
21 Sec. 3. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
22 allocations are made.
23 RETIREMENT SYSTEM, MAINE PUBLIC EMPLOYEES
24 Retirement System - Retirement Allowance Fund 0085
25 Initiative: Provides one-time funds to pay the unfunded actuarial liability created by
26 requiring that cost-of-living increases be applied to a retiree's full benefit amount once the
27 retiree reaches 65 years of age if that person retired from a law enforcement officer position
28 or a probation or parole officer position.
